  "text": "Feature selection models are also widely used in taxonomy learning. For example, attribute selection for building lattices of concepts in [CITATION_1] is done applying specific thresholds on specific information measures on the attributes extracted from corpora. This models uses conditional probabilities, point-wise mutual information, and a selectional-preference-like measure as the one introduced in [CITATION_2] .",
